{
  "name": "sky130_chopper",
  "description": "Silicon (SKY130) chopper amplifier: NMOS input chopper -> NMOS diff pair with diode-connected PMOS loads -> NMOS output chopper -> hold caps, f_chop=250kHz. Clocks drive the switch gates directly (transient_inputs); the differential input drives the VINP/VINN source nodes (node_inputs) - no ideal vsources, so the border-free time-domain PAC/PNoise paths apply (hard-switched conductances converge poorly in sideband-truncated HB). Demodulated differential output (OUTP-OUTN) is DC at gain*(VINP-VINN), gain = -gm1/gm3 (about -1.77). Validated: local transient, PSS orbit, ngspice .tran on the same BSIM4 card + .osdi, and frozen-clock LTI oracles for PAC/PNoise (see tests/test_sky130_chopper.py). The explore block makes this a surrogate-dataset config: python -m core dataset examples/sky130_chopper.json --labels pss,pac,pnoise -n 200 --out chopper_ds labels every candidate with the chopper's periodic figures of merit (conversion gain, band-integrated input-referred noise).",
  "solved": ["G1", "G2", "D1", "D2", "OUTP", "OUTN", "TAIL"],
  "rails": {"GND": 0.0, "VDD": "VDD", "VBIAS": "VB", "VINP": "VINP", "VINN": "VINN",
            "CLK": "VCK", "CLKB": "VCKB"},
  "bias": {"VDD": 1.8, "VB": 0.75, "VINP": 0.905, "VINN": 0.895,
